<br>
When you claim that you have a right to a certain mob in the game you have to consider one main factor.<br>
<br>
Is this mob in a Planish zone or not. Planish zone = 46+ to enter. <br>
<br>
If the mob is in a Planish zone, then the Raid that gets there (the zone) and CLEARS with SUFFICIENT FORCE first gets the mob. <br>
<br>
Example. (planish zone) If Lotus Cult enters the PoG and starts clearing for over a hour. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    NO OTHER GUILD</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> has any claiming rights to Tunare. I don't care how much you bitch, how much you cry, it's their mob. They worked to clear to it, and it's thiers.<br>
<br>
(non planish) Likewise if Vis Maior kills Vindi, Statue of Zek, Idol of Zek, then the Avatar of War belongs to Vis for the first try. <br>
<br>
If we lotus or vis fails, by all rights another guild with sufficient force by the rules of Verant has the right to try.<br>
<br>
The problem here is, Radiant worked hard to clear the path to the wraith and did so with honor. ADD then decides to violate all moral rules and KS a mob from Radiant which is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    WRONG</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
